THE WAY!

course salt
thick cut steak
course black pepper

pile salt high on both sides of steak. let stand for 60 minutes (10 extra minutes if steak is > 2 inches thick). Rince steak and pat dry. Heavily season steak with pepper, and grill to desired doneness.

ALT: 2

Thick cut of beef steak
Beef Bouillon(s)
1 Stick of Butter

Mix cube with a bit of hot butter until a paste is formed. Heavily salt steak for 60 minutes with kosher salt. Rince in sink and pat complely dry. Rub paste into the meat and let stand for 60 minutes. To a very hot skillet, add meat and tilt pan so to create a well for the butter. With a large spoon, laddle hot butter over steak constantly until desired readiness. Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.

ALT: 3

BBQ sauce (w/o salt seasoning)
veg. oil

Take ready steak (above), heavily apply bbq sauce, dip whole steak in a vat of oil, and apply directly to an open flame for a minute on each side. Add back to bbq sauce for a second coat, and apply to a medium - heat of grill and cook until desired doneness. 
